article.headline: Houston 81, LSU 72
article.story: HOUSTON (AP) -- Lanny Smith scored 22 points and Andre Owens had 17 to lead Houston to an 81-72 win over Louisiana State on Tuesday night. Brian Latham added 14 points for the Cougars (8-3), who led by only two at halftime after shooting just more than 31 percent from the field. Houston made nearly 52 percent of its shots in the second half. Brandon Bass had a big night for LSU, scoring 22 points and grabbing a game-high 15 rebounds. Bass was 8-of-13 from the field, as was Antonio Hudson, who scored 20 for the Tigers (5-3). Houston got 20 points from its bench, to only eight for LSU.
